rs are used in federations whose constituent units have them (Canada, Switzerland, and the United States).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFiscal policy. 0aIncome tax. 0aIntergovernmental fiscal relations. 0aIntergovernmental tax relations. 0aTaxation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAlmendral, Violeta Ruiz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlankart, Charles E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFasten, Erik R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilardi, Fabrizio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuimond, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJeffery, Charlie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKübler, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVaillancourt, François, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVaillancourt, François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerdonck, Magali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWasserfallen, Fabio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358809740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773588097423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773588097/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles